Model description

The model is a sum of three Gaussian functions and a linear background function:

Individual Components

1. Elastic Peak (First Gaussian)

where $\sigma_1 = \frac{\text{FWHM}_1}{2\sqrt{2\ln(2)}}$

2. Phonon Peak (Second Gaussian)

where $\sigma_2 = \frac{\text{FWHM}_2}{2\sqrt{2\ln(2)}}$

3. Magnon Peak (Third Gaussian)

where $\sigma_3 = \frac{\text{FWHM}_3}{2\sqrt{2\ln(2)}}$

4. Linear Background

Parameters

  • Elastic peak: $x_{1}$ (center), $A_1$ (amplitude), $\text{FWHM}_1$ (full width at half maximum)
  • Phonon peak: $x_{2}$ (center), $A_2$ (amplitude), $\text{FWHM}_2$ (full width at half maximum)
  • Magnon peak: $x_{3}$ (center), $A_3$ (amplitude), $\text{FWHM}_3$ (full width at half maximum)
  • Background: slope (linear coefficient)

Model 2 Description

Model 2 description

The model is a sum of four Gaussian functions and a linear background function:

Individual Components

1. Elastic Peak (First Gaussian)

where $\sigma_1 = \frac{0.052}{2\sqrt{2\ln(2)}}$ (fixed resolution, centered at zero)

2. Phonon 1 Peak (Second Gaussian) - Low energy phonon

where $\sigma_2 = \frac{0.052}{2\sqrt{2\ln(2)}}$ (fixed resolution)

3. Phonon 2 Peak (Third Gaussian) - High energy phonon

where $\sigma_3 = \frac{0.052}{2\sqrt{2\ln(2)}}$ (fixed resolution)

4. Magnon Peak (Fourth Gaussian)

where $\sigma_4 = \frac{\text{FWHM}_4}{2\sqrt{2\ln(2)}}$ (fitted parameter)

5. Linear Background

Parameters

  • Elastic peak: center fixed at 0.0 eV, $A_1$ (amplitude), FWHM fixed at 0.052 eV
  • Phonon 1 peak: $x_{2}$ (center), $A_2$ (amplitude), FWHM fixed at 0.052 eV
  • Phonon 2 peak: $x_{3}$ (center), $A_3$ (amplitude), FWHM fixed at 0.052 eV
  • Magnon peak: $x_{4}$ (center), $A_4$ (amplitude), $\text{FWHM}_4$ (full width at half maximum)
  • Background: slope (linear coefficient)

Note: The elastic peak is fixed at zero energy with resolution fixed at 0.052 eV. The resolution (FWHM) for both phonon peaks is also fixed at 0.052 eV, while the magnon peak resolution remains a fitted parameter.
